properties.note:name:nl: Fryslân is the official name in both Dutch and Frisian, but the province is colloquially still mostly referred to as Friesland in Dutch.
properties.note:name:en: The exonym Frisia is a long established name, but in English texts the colloquial Dutch (Friesland) and the official Dutch/Frisian endonym (Fryslân) are also used. Frisia can also refer to Frisia Magna, the former kingdom.
properties.note:ISO3166-2: Friesland is a subset (type Province) of the Kingdom of the Netherlands (ISO3166-1 country code NL)
properties.name: Fryslân
